l graph $C^*$-algebras themselves.\n  It follows that the question of Morita equivalence amongst unital graph\n$C^*$-algebras is a decidable one. As immediate examples of applications of our\nresults we revisit the classification problem for quantum lens spaces and\nverify, in the unital case, the Abrams-Tomforde conjectures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Nov 2016 01:43:12 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 25 Aug 2019 15:24:09 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-09-20"}
