um found in Liu et al.(2003). Comparing with the observational results of\nthe hard X-ray bolometric correction factor in a sample of luminous AGNs, we\nsuggest that the value of $\\beta_{\\rm 0}$ is about 100-200 for $\\alpha=0.3$ and\nthe energy fraction $f$ should be larger than $30\\%$ for hard X-ray emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Nov 2016 05:46:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-14"}
