 occured $\\sim$1.2-1.3\nand $\\sim$0.6 Myrs ago, respectively. In addition, we derive abundances of\nargon for the nebula compatible with the solar values and we find a depletion\nof neon and sulfur. The combined analyses of the known kinematics and of the\nnew abundances of the nebula suggest either a helical morphology for the\nnebula, possibly linked to the magnetic geometry, or the occurrence of a binary\nmerger.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Nov 2016 11:40:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-12-09"}
